                      "ep_id": 2454,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/09/26/124137736/5616b6b3139611441609112738d0b013_3450621923866854335.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Иорой",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "When Kitsune Saiguu died during the Cataclysm, Ioroi began to wreak havoc around himself in order to lure his friend out. He stole the ward needed to cleanse the Sacred Sakura, thinking it was an ordinary comb. For this, the Shogun sent Kamuna Harunosuke to deal with Ioroi, who turned the bake-danuki king and the other tanuki of the forest into stone.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2541,
                      "icon_url": "https://upload-static.hoyoverse.com/hoyolab-wiki/2023/04/14/237301566/fbd2dfe0d5891487065fbfb1059b6ed1_7372750484125757394.png",
                      "menu_id": 10,
                      "name": "Ханатирусато",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Although Kamuna Harunosuke knew that Hanachirusato was not the real Kitsune Saiguu but filth, he helped her with the Sacred Sakura Cleansing ritual and didn't harm her.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Onmyoudou",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "After returning from Liyue to Inazuma, Kamuna Harunosuke created the Onmyoudou Art, which uses special paper seals to harness elemental power. Harunosuke created the Mystic Onmyou Chamber to practice the art and train warriors, but the chamber was later disbanded.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
